headline: The singular Georges de La Tour at the Musée Jacquemart-André
description: Some 30 works attributed to the French painter, whose life remains little known, are on display in Paris. In the absence of a clear chronology, the paintings have been categorized by subject − both secular and sacred.

headline: The Bayeux Tapestry, a barometer of Franco-British relations
description: France's decision to lend the nearly 1,000-year-old tapestry to the United Kingdom represents part of the long and tumultuous relationship between the two countries; Brexit supporters had even turned the tapestry into a symbol of national humiliation.

headline: An abbey in southern France rescued by contemporary art
